## One architectural enhancement I'd add

Given your long-term vision, I would introduce an **AI Orchestration Layer** between the frontend and individual AI providers. Instead of your Cloud Functions calling Gemini or GPT directly, every request would go through a single internal service:

```
Frontend
        │
        ▼
AI Orchestrator
        │
 ┌──────┼────────┐
 ▼      ▼        ▼
Gemini  GPT-5   Rule Engine
(Document) (Reasoning) (Validation)
        │
        ▼
Normalized Quote
        │
        ▼
Comparison Engine
```

This gives you several long-term benefits:

* Swap AI providers without changing business logic.
* A/B test different models.
* Retry with a fallback provider if one fails.
* Centralize logging, token usage, latency, and cost tracking.
* Introduce caching for identical or repeated quote analyses.

For a platform you intend to grow into India's leading AI-powered solar advisory service, this separation will make the architecture significantly more maintainable and resilient as both your traffic and AI usage increase.
